examples.en: Add a few drops of lemon juice.
He squeezed the bottle until a few drops came out.
Drops of water sparkled in the sunlight.
At night the temperature drops below zero.

A cat licked up the drops spilt on the floor.
On his way home he drops into a pub, and gets some booze.
Moisture in the air condenses to form tiny drops of water.
I lay five to two, Mathilda drops in a year. (W. M. Thackeray)
As the first drops of rain began to fall, Michael started to run.
On the left the ground drops away, giving a view over the rooftops.

We'll wait till the wind drops (=blows less strongly) before we put the tent up.
